This memorandum, issued on April 30, 2009, delegates certain functions under sections 603-604 and 699 of the Foreign Relations Authorization Act, Fiscal Year 2003, to the Secretary of State. The President, Barack Obama, delegates these functions to the Secretary of State through the authority vested in him by the Constitution and the laws of the United States. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to transmit this determination and certification to the appropriate committees of Congress and publish it in the Federal Register.